<div class="modal fade" id="{{modal_id}}">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <form action="./{{jobId}}" method="post">
        <input type="hidden" name="job_id" value="{{jobId}}" />
        <input type="hidden" name="mechanic_id" id="mechanic_id" value="{{currentUserId}}" />
        <input type="hidden" name="bid_expires" id="bid_expires" value="7 days" />
        <input type="hidden" name="bid_id" value="{{bid.id}}" />
        <div class="modal-header">
          <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
          <h4 class="modal-title">Your bid parameters</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-3">
              <label for="bid_amount">Bid amount</label>
              <div class="input-group">
                <input type="text" name="bid_amount" id="bid_amount" class="form-control" value="{{bid.amount}}" />
                <span class="input-group-addon">USD</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-8">
              <p>
                Often, the manager of a job (called a designer) is more concerned 
                with the expected quality of your work (based on your notes below) 
                than the amount you bid.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-8">
              <label for="notes">Notes</label>
              <textarea class="form-control" name="notes" id="notes">{{bid.notes}}</textarea>
              <p>
                Your bid will expire in 7 days. If you would like to 
                indicate a shorter expiration, please mention it in your notes.
              </p>              
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <p>
                This is where you describe your approach on how to get 
                this job done. These notes are one tool Designers (job managers) use to 
                compare bidders and decide who is right for the job.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <label for="done_in">Done in</label>
              <p>It will take me this amount of time to achieve the expected functionality</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-8">
              <input type="hidden" name="done_in" id="done_in" value="{{bid.time_to_complete}}" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-footer">
          {{^editBid}}
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" name="place_bid">Place bid</button>
          {{/editBid}}
          {{#editBid}}
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" name="edit_bid">Edit bid</button>
          {{/editBid}}
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
